node.text:
As the Pleiades star cluster rises, it signals the start of Matariki, the Māori New Year. Matariki is about celebrating the present and looking forward to the future while remembering the past. 'Kia whakatōmuri te haere whakamua' - I walk backwards into the future with my eyes fixed on my past. 

How would you make your Matariki special this year? #MatarikiMoment ✨

node.text: The @americascup was set to be a moment that brought the world together, in New Zealand – yet we are oceans apart. So we called in an old friend, @SirRodStewart, to rally our nation to singalong with him, and send a message of togetherness around the world. 🎵⛵ #RocktheDock #AC36 #NewZealand

#NewZealand #DoSomethingNewNZ #NZMustDo​

node.text:
Muriwai is one of only three gannet/tākapu colonies on the New Zealand mainland. To attract a seabird colony you need a consistently strong wind – something which Muriwai definitely has!​

Can you guess how many pairs of gannets nest on the cliffs from August to March each year? ​

#DoSomethingNewNZ #NZMustDo
